<p>
  Need to match a color from a logo, photo, or screenshot? An image color picker (also called an eyedropper) lets you click any pixel and instantly get the exact color code — in HEX, RGB, and HSL.
</p>

<h2>What is an Image Color Picker?</h2>

<p>
  An image color picker samples the color of a specific pixel in an image. It's the web equivalent of the eyedropper tool in Photoshop or Figma. Instead of guessing a hex code, you click the exact pixel and get the precise value.
</p>

<h2>How to Pick a Color from an Image Online</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Open the <a href="/imagewonder/image-color-picker">Image Color Picker</a>.</li>
  <li>Upload any JPG, PNG, WebP, or screenshot.</li>
  <li>Hover over the image to preview colors in real time.</li>
  <li>Click any pixel to lock the color and see HEX, RGB, and HSL values.</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Copy</strong> next to the format you need.</li>
  <li>Build a palette of recently picked colors at the bottom.</li>
</ol>

